    "name": "Natural Selection",
    "profile": "R&B/Synth Pop duo active from 1989 to 1992.\r\n\r\nThe duo was started by Elliot Erickson and originally included singer Steve Bryant (Kallsen) where they recorded a remake of Nik Kershaw's \"[m=86863]\". The single was first picked up independently by KDWB's Brian Phillips and started to create a buzz around the Minnesota/Wisconsin radio scene. This was the original catalyst which brought attention to the band Natural Selection. Bryant left the band and was replaced by Frederick Thomas.\r\n\r\nThe song \"[m=168088]\" sat unfinished until Erickson began working on it again in 1989. The rap was originally recorded by [a33345], a friend of the duo who improvised the rap in the studio. In 1990, the version with Chavez doing the raps was a local hit on Minnesota's WLOL-FM, where Erickson worked as a remix engineer.\r\n\r\nOnce Natural Selection was signed to a recording contract, Chavez's raps were re-recorded by [a58266], because Chavez was by then under contract with Paisley Park Records.\r\n\r\n",
